org.openbel.framework.tools.pkam
Interface PKAMSerializationService

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultPKAMSerializationService
public interface PKAMSerializationService

PKAMSerializationService defines a service to serialize a KamStore KAM database into Portable KAM format.

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

Method Detail

serializeKAM

void serializeKAM(String kamName,
                  String filePath,
                  String password)
                  throws PKAMSerializationFailure
Serializes KAM, identified by kamName, to a file, identified by fileName, in Portable KAM (PKAM) format.

Parameters:
kamName - String, the kam name to serialize, which cannot be null
filePath - String, the file path to store serialized data, which cannot be null
password - String, the password to use when encrypting the KAM, which cannot be null
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if either kamName, filePath, or password is null
PKAMSerializationFailure

deserializeKAM

void deserializeKAM(String kamName,
                    String filePath,
                    String password,
                    boolean noPreserve)
                    throws PKAMSerializationFailure
Deserializes KAM from a file, identified by filePath, in Portable KAM format.

Parameters:
kamName - String, the kam name to save the deserialized KAM to, which can be null, indicating the kam name should be read from the file
filePath - String, the file path where the Portable KAM is stored, which cannot be null
password - String, the password to use when decrypting the KAM, which cannot be null
noPreserve - boolean, the noPreserve option needed once the portable KAM file's kam name is read
Throws:
PKAMSerializationFailure - Thrown if an error occurred deserializing the KAM located at filePath
InvalidArgument - Thrown if filePath or password is null
